Class PBInfoEvent

java.lang.Object
org.example.galaxy_trucker.ClientServer.Messages.PBInfoEvent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Event
public class PBInfoEvent extends Object implements Event
The PBInfoEvent class represents an event containing various information related to a player's board in a game. It implements the Event interface and can be processed by an EventVisitor. This class is designed to encapsulate the player's status and details such as credits, total value, damage, energy, and other associated information. This class is a part of a polymorphic event system utilizing Jackson annotations for serialization and deserialization.

  • Constructor Details

    • PBInfoEvent

      public PBInfoEvent()
      Default constructor for the PBInfoEvent class. This no-argument constructor initializes an instance of the PBInfoEvent class, which represents a specific type of event in the system. This class serves as part of the event-handling mechanism, facilitating communication and interaction within the application architecture. The PBInfoEvent is designed to encapsulate information related to the state of a player board and implements the Event interface to allow for visitor-based processing. This constructor may be used for creating instances of PBInfoEvent before the actual properties are populated or when no specific initialization is required at the time of object creation.

    • PBInfoEvent

      public PBInfoEvent(int damage, int credits, int exposedConnectors, int[] shield, int numHumans, int enginePower, double plasmaDrillsPower, int energy, boolean purpleAlien, boolean brownAlien, int totValue)
      Constructs a new PBInfoEvent instance with detailed information about a player's board state.
      Parameters:
      damage - the amount of damage sustained
      credits - the number of credits available
      exposedConnectors - the number of exposed connectors
      shield - the shield values as an array of integers
      numHumans - the number of humans present
      enginePower - the power of the engine
      plasmaDrillsPower - the power of the plasma drills
      energy - the amount of energy available
      purpleAlien - whether a purple alien is present (true if present, false otherwise)
      brownAlien - whether a brown alien is present (true if present, false otherwise)
      totValue - the total value associated with this event
